a or in industrial environments students may enter the department with the intention of obtaining either a ms or a phd or both degrees mailing address department of applied physics 348 via pueblo mall stanford university stanford ca 94305 4090 phone 650 723 4027 location center for nanoscale science and engineering applied physics office suite rooms 116 118 map department chair professor hideo mabuchi phone 650 723 0201 or 650 723 4027 hmabuchi stanford edu administrative staff paula p perron department administrator phone 650 723 4027 email pperron stanford edu claire k nicholas administrative associate phone 650 723 4028 email claireni stanford edu 143 15 temperature dependence a k from 0.36 to 2 k of penetration depth in the superconductor lafepo as measured by the fisher and moler labs 25 th order of high harmonic generation observed in a bulk crystal by reis lab news and events 7th annual western conference for undergraduate women in physics report aps fellows block hwang and suzuki 2012 urbanek postdoctoral fellowship competition junior faculty position in x ray scattering and spectroscopy see all applied physics posts how complex are biological systems imaging nonequilibrium phonons intense laser matter interactions results in high order harmonic generation in solids quantum ready engineering graduate admissions 2010 11 see all applied physics themes nanoscience and quantum engineering lasers and accelerators condensed matter physics experimental and theoretical biophysics browse all topic tags navigate home about contact faculty alumni academic programs admissions news & events applied physics posts sign up for our email newsletter contact us visiting address nano center rooms 116 118 map online campus map phone 650 723 4027 email pperron stanford edu mailing address department of applied physics 348 via pueblo mall stanford university stanford ca 94305 4090 all content stanford university all rights reserved
